SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1057
By Haile
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Glenda Akin on
breaking the Guinness World Record for the
longest career by a female teacher in the same
school.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should specially recognize those outstanding teachers
who have devoted their careers to providing the highest quality education for Tennessee's
students; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Glenda Akin, who has set the Guinness
World Record for the longest career by a female teacher in the same school, having taught at
Westmoreland High School for more than sixty-one years; and
WHEREAS, beginning her tenure as a teacher in 1963, Glenda Akin shaped the lives of
generations of students at Westmoreland High School, where the school library has been
renamed in her honor; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Akin was an inspiration to the faculty, staff, and students of
Westmoreland High School, and her friendship and counsel were highly valued by those who
were fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Glenda Akin truly epitomizes the dedicated educator who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Glenda Akin on breaking
the Guinness World Record for the longest career by a female teacher in the same school,
SJR1057
